<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-05-29T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-05-29T18:00:00-05:00" n="34" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d34">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">796.5–MAP/5–2951: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Embassy in the Philippines</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-05-29T19:00:00-04:00">May
                                        29, 1951—7 p. m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <gloss target="#t_Toisa1">Toisa</gloss> 2957. Emb need not concern
                                itself about the continued availability beyond Jun 30 1951 of the
                                $10 million made available to Dept of Def under <gloss target="#t_MDAP1">MDAP</gloss> for emergency assistance to the
                                Philippines. Official records will show that the entire $10 million
                                was expended from the appropriation concerned during May. Funds were
                                transferred to a Dept of Def special deposit account without fiscal
                                year limitation and will continue available for the purposes
                                intended until exhausted. Advise Gen Hobbs.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>